  "prompt": "Which state in Nepal speaks pure Hindi?",
  "response": "There is no state in Nepal that speaks \"pure Hindi.\" Nepal is a linguistically diverse country with Nepali as its official language. While Hindi is understood and spoken by some people, especially in urban areas and among certain communities, it is not the primary language in any state or region of Nepal. The concept of \"pure Hindi\" itself can be subjective, as languages naturally evolve and incorporate elements from other languages over time.",
